Product name: William Morris Tie - Floral Tie - Men's Neckties - Groomsman Tie - Wedding Tie - William Morris Art
Description:
William Morris Tie
William Morris was an English textile designer, poet, novelist, translator, and socialist activist in the 1800s. His art was ornate and beautiful as seen on this carefully screen printed tie. 
This is one of Morris' beautiful patterns expertly screen printed on a microfiber, Umo Lorenzo necktie. The design is is printed on the bottom 27 inches of the tie, which means it's all that will be showing when the tie is tied. 
Choose between black or a muted green ink. Some tie colors aren't available with green ink as it won't show up. See what's available in the drop down menu.
3.5 inches at it's widest point, 58 inches long
*************************************
SHIPPING and LEAD TIMES/TURNAROUND
In order to be able to offer many color options for each necktie, all ties are made to order and take 1-7 days to print before shipping. If you need us to get it out the door right away, please let us know and we can usually accommodate.
Orders in the U.S. usually take 2-4 days to arrive once shipped. You'll receive a tracking number once it's shipped.
INTERNATIONAL orders are shipped USPS First Class and generally take 5-9 business days once printed and shipped. Some countries tend to hold packages in customs for longer periods, in which case the package may take an extra 5-8 business days in transit. In rare cases, packages can be held up even longer due to your country's import laws.
If you have any questions about our neckties, designs, shipping, or anything else, please contact us!
